<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9042">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9042">
Traditionally, the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Orthocentrinae">Orthocentrinae</taxonomicName>
comprised a tightly-knit group of genera related to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthocentrus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Orthocentrus</taxonomicName>
but now includes many genera of the former ' 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Microleptinae">Microleptinae</taxonomicName>
' sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Townes, HK" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="1 - 372" title="The genera of Ichneumonidae, Part 4" volume="17" year="1971">Townes (1971)</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wahl, D. B." journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="27 - 52" title="A review of the mature larvae of Diplazontinae, with notes on larvae of Acaenitinae and Orthocentrinae and proposal of two new subfamilies (Insecta: Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae)" volume="24" year="1990">Wahl 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Distribution data taken from BMNH, NMS (det. J.F. Perkins and GRB), UM, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rossem, G. van" journalOrPublisher="Spixiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="149 - 170" title="A revision of some western Palaearctic oxytorine genera. Part II. Genus Eusterinx (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae)" volume="5" year="1982">Rossem (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rossem, G. van" journalOrPublisher="Contributions of the American Entomological Institute" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="153 - 165" title="A revision of Western Palearctic oxytorine genera. Part III. Genus Proclitus (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae)" volume="20" year="1983">Rossem (1983a)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rossem, G. van" journalOrPublisher="Tijdschrift voor Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="49 - 108" title="A revision of Western Palaearctic oxytorine genera. Part VI. (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae)" volume="130" year="1987">Rossem (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rossem, G. van" journalOrPublisher="Tijdschrift voor Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="103 - 112" title="A revision of Palaearctic oxytorine genera. Part VII. (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae)" volume="131" year="1988">Rossem (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Dasch, C." journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="1 - 470" title="The ichneumon-flies of America north of Mexico. Pt. 12. Subfamilies Microleptinae, Helictinae, Cylloceriinae and Oxytorinae (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae)" volume="52" year="1992">Dasch (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, with additional references given.
</paragraph>
